{#
  Companion content — off-site deep-dive content for the current page.
  Documented in STYLE_GUIDE.md §6.12.

  Distinct from the Related component (§6.10):
    - Related = lateral moves WITHIN the site (other pages here)
    - Companion = vertical moves OFF the site (longer-form treatments
      of THIS page's specific topic — Substack articles, YouTube
      videos, podcast appearances, etc.)

  Page front-matter declares `companion:` as an array. Each entry:

    companion:
      - url: https://lastcoinstanding.substack.com/p/...
        title: "Why I built the Power Law calculator"
        kind: substack                       # substack | youtube | podcast | external
        desc: "The story behind the tool, in long-form."

  Renders nothing if `companion:` is missing or empty — graceful no-op.
  All entries open in a new tab (target=_blank, rel=noopener).

  Visual treatment is intentionally quieter than Related —
  supplementary content, not a lateral suggestion. Lives below the
  Related block when both are present on the same page.
#}

{%- if companion and companion.length > 0 -%}
<aside class="companion-block">
  <div class="companion-label">Going deeper</div>
  <div class="companion-list">
{%- for c in companion %}
  {%- set kind = c.kind or 'external' -%}
    <a href="{{ c.url }}" class="companion-item kind-{{ kind }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <div class="companion-kind">
        {%- if kind == 'substack' -%}Substack
        {%- elif kind == 'youtube' -%}Video
        {%- elif kind == 'podcast' -%}Podcast
        {%- else -%}External
        {%- endif -%}
        <span class="companion-arrow">&nearr;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="companion-text">
        <h4 class="companion-title">{{ c.title | safe }}</h4>
        {%- if c.desc %}<p class="companion-desc">{{ c.desc | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
      </div>
    </a>
{%- endfor %}
  </div>
</aside>
{%- endif -%}
